## 4. Affected Parties — Notification Plan

If the FRIA identifies that natural persons' rights could be materially affected by an AI decision taken with one of these systems, those persons are informed:

- at the point of interaction (see AI Usage Policy);
- in the privacy notice;
- and, for any decision contested, in writing within 14 days of the contestation request.

---

## 5. Review Cadence

This FRIA is to be reviewed:

- on each material change to a listed system (provider swap, new data category processed, tier change);
- on each substantial change to the deployment (new user group, new feature relying on the system);
- at minimum annually;
- following any reported serious incident.

